	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Damn it they did it again.<br />
<br />
"The one down side to the new system is that there will be a slight decrease in experience for those who do not group, and only for those who do so in Planes of Power zones."<br />
<br />
*** is SoE have against a soloer, can someone  answer me this? /sigh<br />
<br />
Oh well, atleast we can take solice in this...<br />
<br />
"The "blue to 65" range has been increased as far as level 50" <br />
<br />
Im very glad that is finaly being tested. This is a large step to making many zones more usable to a level 65ish player again. props for a good choice in testing it.<br />
<br />
But man , i still cant help being a lil down as the soloers get shafted again. Didnt they already decrease the soloers exp ? I know then did then eased the ratio but i thought it never went back to what it was, it was still tweaked against the soloer. So is this yet another case of penilizing the soloer furthur ? Or is it just a reimplementation of what they did before.<br />
<br />
Either way I think we all need to get some feedback going on this cause we made a difference last time and i sure hate to see soloers ( as im one of them ) be choked out. Its not really far to classes that cant get groups easy and there isnt much a point to doing it to people who can solo well either.  Make goruping worth more yes, but not by slowing down the soloers, this game takes enough time to level at the higher end (50-65). I think this type of tactic is just going to drive people away. <br />
<br />
I hate to say it, cause i like EQ and think EQ2 is going to be more my style then WoW, but if im going to be kept down for the sake of people that group then im heading to a less time consuming game like Wow when it comes out.<br />
<br />
I guess we need to see how much difference the changes make. <br />
<br />
/waits for some test server player feedback</p>
	
	
	
	
	
