	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Here is a intresting thought.<br />
<br />
<br />
Why not making exping in games like EQ super easy. BUT... make much enjoyable content and quests that are very much appropriate for those levels. Do not make the game rewarding for those who have the super best gear and slave all night and day and quit their jobs to live EQ, but simply make the rewards right for the level and it only allows you to access quests and content right for that level. Make the game so the higher end content isnt more fun or challanging or something to race forward to, make each step enjoyable and not just a build up to a later part of the game. <br />
<br />
This way you just enjoy the game and when you wanna move on to new content you grab a group and zip up a few levels then go around doing quests and battling mobs and building towns and doing tradeskills and FUN things again.<br />
<br />
Ehh, just my dream fro a RPG i guess.</p>
	
	
	
	
