<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>finaljustice</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Oracle<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jul 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Once again, let's look at the bottom line.  This is a game that's been out over three years.  It's been played (if each subscription is played an average of 1 hour per day) over 300 Million Man hours.  SWG and WoW are just over the horizon and Sony's worried about loss of revinue.<br />
<br />
So they introduce several things designed to not hurt anybody.  They open up tier 2 and several tier 3 zones to anyone who wants to go there.  They slightly decrease PoP EXP, while massively increasing group EXP.  They also open up many zones to 60+ that have been closed for awhile.<br />
<br />
Who does this hurt?  Soloists who have been "doing it THIS way and I don't want to change!" and groups that have been exp'ing "HERE and I don't want any damn n00bz in competition with me!"<br />
<br />
Either of those aren't likely to cancel their subscriptions due to this change.  People who were stuck in Tier 1, getting crappy exp were.  Bored with so little loot in PoP zones?  Do what we do every once in awhile....  We send 2 3-person groups into Seb and handle every single mob on the first floor (except those in the crypt).  It's hella fun and very fluid (as well as about 3-4K per person, per hour).</p>
	
	
	
