	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" /><br />
*** is SoE have against a soloer, can someone answer me this? <br />
<hr size="1" /></blockquote>The correct question is *** did SOE have against group dependent classes, can you answer me this?<br />
<br />
Think about a Rogue. Why should they receive less experience for being reliant on groups for exp? Why shouldn't a group(something that VI, then SOE claim is their "vision") mean as much exp as soloing? Shouldn't there be a reward for grouping instead of thinking to yourself "Man, I could group with those guys but it will just kill my exp."?<br />
<br />
Both should be equally viable as a means of experience. What this does is to partially erase the <b>penalty</b> on grouping - however for what it's worth I do believe it is a mistake to nerf the PoP modifiers.<br />
<br />
Obviously SOE has been reading the paladin boards(hey, least they listen to some classes - right?):<br />
<br />
<a href="http://pub148.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm21.showMessage?topicID=457.topic" target="_blank">http://pub148.ezboard.com/fpaladins...picID=457.topic</a></p>
	
	
	
	
	
