<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Flargly</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Nov 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I posted a reply on the necro boards (My baby necro is about to ding 50)<br />
<br />
Anyways the necros seem split. Half like it cause they can now pet solo dark blues again, or they have all thier aa and exp doesnt matter. The other half realizes this as a massive nerf (which it is).<br />
<br />
People, think about this a second. I'll sumarize from my post on the necro board whats REALLY going on here.<br />
<br />
1) SOE made a mistake with PoP exp bonus. They could not continue to keep adding bigger and better bonuses each expansion. LoY came out and lvl 50's really arent playing in it. PoP Tier 1 exp is jsut so much better. To combat this in upcoming expansions they will jsut remove the exp modifier from pop, while upping the group modifier. Now you can exp ANYWHERE there are dark blues, and providing you are in a group get PoP like exp or better.<br />
<br />
2) This is a HUGE fundamental change to the game. HUGE. Let me repeat that HUGE. Sit and think about it a second. Nothing they could do would change the game more.<br />
<br />
3) Soloers made great exp but they took on large risk. A necro soloing in PoP dies when an add shows up and he fails a FD. Fact of life. Thats offset the by faster than average exp. Tweaking this is natural, elimating risk/reward is not. Now that same necro is going to see the PoP exp bonus disapear. The mobs wont be any easier. The risk is the same. A 6 man group, who, by the way, are balanced around the trinity and 3 dps classes wont want the necro. They will be able to pull PoP exp ANYWHERE at NO RISK. The soloer is now forced to group with a class thats been developed and blanced for 3+ years as a soloer. No group wants him, and his solo exp has been nerfed. Good job SOE.<br />
<br />
4) EXP exploits. Oh let me count the ways. Jesus. Think about it. The ultimate exp group is now 4 wizrds, a tank and a cleric. go to a zone with low Dark blues that do little damage.. 48-52 range say in Loy. Pull 10 or 20 of them, wizards unload AOE, with the exp bonus now thats INSANE exp. Do the math. It blows away anything in PoP WITH NO RISK. sure you dont get the lvl 5 and under exp bonus but who careses? its an extra 25-50% Seriously? you are getting a 80% bonus already split only 5 ways and you just slaughtered 10-20 mobs in seconds, and you can keep it up forever? Remember the Fungus grove fiascos? I mean comon SOE, pull your head out of your ass.<br />
<br />
You think chanter charm exp was insane, wait till you see the totally unblanced groups that form now to farm exp and clear WHOLE ZONES at a time. The problem is they are manufacturing exp out of the air. Its a novel idea but in a large game it doesnt work unless the whole game has been balanced from the start against it. EQ never was and there is no way it can ever be.<br />
<br />
The thing is, there is NO way to fix the above without totally fubaring the whole game. The game is BALANCED around the current exp system. Altering it skews so many things in favor of some classes, and so many things against other classes, you will see a huge shift in teh player base. And thats not good.<br />
<br />
I'll shift back to playing my shaman more. Others wil lshift to thier clers and tanks. It'll be a 1 dimensional game with little fun. <img src="images/smilies/frown.gif" border="0" alt="" title="frown" smilieid="2" /></p>
	
	
	
	
	
