	<p>I still see one major reason beyond all others that grouping exp should be better then soloing exp.<br />
<br />
Soloing i log on, move to some random spot, and start to solo (sometimes grabbing a kei).<br />
<br />
When I group, especially not on my shaman it can involve 30 minutes to an hour to put a group together, all that time a soloer can get exp. Even if they exp faster, that 30 minute to an hour head start really helps. Not to mention the time invesment  isn't there since they can log in 2 hours where as I'd need 3 and a half to equal them out.<br />
<br />
Now lets say I get into an established group (assuming im on my paladin), 15 minutes later chanter has to go afk to put his kid to bed, crap no slow. Ok well 15 to 20 minutes he comes back and we can start pulling, but oh crap our cleric has to leave. Hmm well we don't have any backup healing, so we need to get a replacement. Even a shaman would do, but there is only a bard, a wizard, and a beastlord lfg at the moment. Screwed.<br />
<br />
30 minutes later I've bribed my friend, the 65 druid with 200 AAs to stop soloing loroks and come heal for my group, of course now i owe him one because he is slowing his exp gain for me.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
